ownedComment.body:
The Party Revenue Sharing Model ABE contains party revenue sharing models, and their specifications, that define how revenue is shared by and enterprise with one or more other parties. Revenue sharing models are a key component revenue sharing agreements.
Product Offering Price ABE entities are used to represent amounts of revenue shared. For example, an enterprise may charge 10 euros for an offering and share a flat 4 euros with another party, such as an application developer. For configurable offerings the revenue shared may be dependent on those features chosen by the party who acquires the offering. In this case the revenue shared is also governed by the configuration of the party's product.
